[codex] +> Thus, the current landscape does not simply make the paper less timely; it helps clarify when descriptive feedback should be more or less likely to matter. We now explain that descriptive feedback should be most influential when past selection patterns raise active concerns about prejudice, and less influential in contexts where those concerns are absent, muted, or explicitly rejected.
